flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: New vehicle program kickoff, engineering change notification, or planned end-of-life/parts transition enters S&OP planning horizon (initial program phase defined).]
  A --> N1[Stream: STREAMS - Ingest program, BOM, capacity, orders, supplier and campaign data into Subject Areas]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: Cortex Auto Forecast - Generate baseline and scenario demand forecasts and ramp curves for the new program]
  N2 --> N3[Cortex: RCA Service - Run RCA to surface engineering-change impacts and supplier risk vectors]
  N3 --> N4{Agent: Process Builder + Agent Team - Orchestrate multi-scenario trade-off evaluation and recommendation via agentic workflow}
  N4 -->|Primary| N5[PB: Remote Functions + CWB Lifecycle - Execute approved plan: writeback production schedules & POs and create CWB for exceptions]
  N5 --> N6[UI: UI Screen / dashboard - Surface final plan and KPIs to S&OP stakeholders and schedule monitoring]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Coordinated launch plan committed in SAP S/4HANA with minimized incremental COGS, protected launch revenue targets, reduced working capital through staged inventory and supplier commitments, and an auditable approval trail with contingency scenarios.]
  N4 -->|Key supplier capacity shortfall disco...| B1[Process Builder triggers alternative sourcing and phased launch subprocess; Agent Team evaluates cost vs. delay trade-offs and proposes phased SKU sequencing or expedited logistics with higher COGS]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Revised ramp plan with mitigations (phased launch or higher-cost supply path) and updated financial impact communicated to stakeholders]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Forecast scenario uncertainty above t...| B2[Agent Team generates multiple commit-level scenarios, increases buffer recommendations, and requests interim marketing alignment to smooth demand]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Conservative commit adopted with contingency inventory and a plan to re-plan at next cadence, reducing risk to revenue and minimizing overstock]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Stakeholder overrides recommended pla...| B3[CWB Lifecycle captures override rationale, Process Builder runs impact recalculation, and Remote Functions write approved changes to SAP S/4HANA with audit trail]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Approved override applied operationally with documented business justification and updated KPIs for post-launch review]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]